  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      MR Elastography is a new technique aimed at non-invasively measuring the stiffness of
      tissues. It has recently given interesting results in the assessment of liver fibrosis.

      The objectives of the current study are:

        1. to develop an imaging protocol for MR Elastography of the kidneys;

        2. To calculate the stiffness of normal kidneys;

        3. To evaluate the variability of the measurements of kidney stiffness by repeating the
           procedure twice on the same volunteers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
